This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 09:40 AM Defendant Jay T. White in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court asks White if he has counsel yet. White states he has Breanna Halyburton and she was just in the Courtroom and went to talk to another client. Recess to wait for Attorney Halyburton to see if she is on this case as well. Back on record at 9:56 AM. Attorney Halyburton appears specially now. Halyburton - defendant does still qualify and she will not be appointed to the case, waives reading of it, enters NG pleas. Court accepts plea, continues bond, set for JT.
Adjourned initial appearance on April 27, 2022 at 09:30 am.
No consumption of alcohol, must submit to a request toprovide a sample of the alcohol level in his system to law enforcement.

09:19 AM Defendant Jay T. White in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews file - asks defendant why he was not here on 2/8/22. White states he was sick and did not have transportation. Court mentions Zoom. White states he did not have a phone. Court comfirms address. White has complaint. Court reads charges and penalties and right to attorney and court appointed attorney. White states he has Atty Halyburton and thought she would be here today. State checks hallway for Attorney Halyburton. Atty Halyburton now appears at 9:23 AM, will appear specially today and will probably be appointed but will look into that. Court - bond - $500.00 cash, no consumption of alcohol, must submit to a request toprovide a sample of the alcohol level in his system to law enforcement. Court sets for AIA on 4/27/22 at 9:30 AM.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for April 27, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Adjourned initial appearance on April 13, 2022 at 09:00 am.

09:56 AM Defendant Jay T. White not in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CC and CR appear by video. State based on failure to appear, summons went out, asks for warrant, body or $500, FC only. Court so orders.
Released without bond. PC not established within 48 hours of arrest
